==English==
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''nucleoside'''
# {{biochemistry}} an organic molecule in which a [[nitrogenous]] [[heterocyclic]] [[base]] (or [[nucleobase]]), which can be either a double-ringed [[purine]] or a single-ringed [[pyrimidine]], is covalently attached to a five-carbon [[pentose]] [[sugar]] ([[deoxyribose]] in [[DNA]] or [[ribose]] in [[RNA]]). When the [[phosphate]] group is [[covalent]]ly attached to the [[pentose]] [[sugar]], it forms a [[nucleotide]].
